channel.title: Port-Forwarding issues
channel.description:
I can't open the port (43594) no matter what I do. I've tried everything I know, read, or been told. I have a separate Modem & router. Modem- EQ-660R-F1 Router- Netgear WNDR3400 Yes, I have followed Portforwarding.com without success. I have added exception in the fire, even turned it completely off. (also disabled the firewall in my modem) I've tried things like turning Qos on and adding a rule. I've opened the NAT in my router. Disabled DOS protection and port scan. Disabled IGMP Proxying. I've setup No-ip. I've tried the Utorrent thing.
Now, I really need someones help. you can't say I didn't try lol. I'm thinking it has to do with my IP somewhere. But I honesly don't know to much on dealing with IP's. And what ones are supposed to match up with this and that. So if anyone can TV me and check things out I would appreciate that. Thanks guys
